{
  "texts": [
    "28 Finally, note that a Heyting algebra may be defined as a bounded implicative lattice.",
    "Every finite bounded implicative semilattice is a Heyting algebra, but not every infinite bounded implicative semilattice is a Heyting algebra.When we add an accessibility relation R i to ⟨A, ≤⟩, we need one more definition.",
    "Definition 4.37 ( i Operation).",
    "Given a poset ⟨A, ≤⟩ with minimum ⊥ and a binary relation R i on A, define a partial operation i on A as follows: for y ∈ A, if the set ■ i ↓y, i.e., {x ∈ A | R i (x) ⊆ ↓y} (Definition 2.1), is nonempty and contains a maximum element, then i y = max(■ i ↓y).",
    "If ■ i ↓y is empty, then i y = ⊥."
  ]
}